[HFMD is frequently reported, and is generally a mild disease, predominantly of children. It is often caused by coxsackie virus A16, but other enteroviruses may be implicated. Virus spreads quickly in daycare and other such facilities, increasing risk for children in that age group. They usually build up immunity to the virus after being exposed, but older children and adults may become infected. - Mod.LK

